<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-05T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-05T10:00:00-05:00" n="897" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d897">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/320</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Peru</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MB1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-05T10:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 4.02 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s circular of March 23, 7 p.m. In reply to Legation’s note,
                            Minister of Foreign Affairs says that Peruvian Government gives to
                            Government of the United States most complete assurances that the ships
                            which the American Government has decided to dedicate to commercial
                            traffic between the United States and Peru will enjoy [in] Peruvian
                            ports fullest facilities, so that in no case can they be subjected to
                            delays or exigencies of bond arising from litigation which might come up
                            over their possession.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MB1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>